,Recommended,211740,14312279,"Posted: 3 February, 2015",all,The Medicine Peddler,"My eyes are unclouded by nostalgia. I was born too late to have experienced the theif series in it's prime. But even to me, a series newcomer, this game has more than stood the test of time.Pros:+ Garret is a great protagonist.+ Amazing stealth gameplay+ With an HD texture pack installed, the game is still atmospheric 15 years after it's release.+ Great steampunk setting+ Father Karras is a great antagonist+ Humanized enemy guards with their own worries, lives and dreams, a rarity today. Makes you feel awful about killing them more than any forced karma system ever could.+ Encourages acutally going through a level without anyone noticing you, rather than the modern approach of (pick off guards one by one do it do it do it)+ Huge expansive levels with tons of little details and secrets.+ Combat is incredibly difficult when directly confronting guards. and thats a good thing.+ the material the floor is made of, and how loud your footsteps would be on it, is a huge gameplay mechanic.+ Voice acting is pretty great considering how old the game is.Cons:- while dated voice acting is to be expected, some of the voices are pretty awful even by early 2000s standards. Mostly the female ones.- Inventory wheels can be intensely frustrating when you have to switch items quickly."
