,Recommended,211740,32226704,Posted: 6 June,all,ChillyWilly,"A fantastic stealth game which fans of the genre will still love to this day. If you do not enjoy stealth games, this won't change your mind. Thief 2 is all about staying in the shadows and navigation. Combat is present, but ill advised as you are so pathetically weak that a single guard is likely to end you. What you must do is use a plethora of tools with multiple uses to your advantage in getting through a situation.Due to its pure focus on stealth, the enemy AI holds up. They'll patrol, they'll linger, they'll get into banter with each other, they may even be hostile with one another depending on your level. Speaking of the levels, they are simply enormous, packed full of secrets, loot, and supplies you may put to use. Monsters from the first game which you had to fight have been all but removed, which takes away plenty of the tedium they presented, along with their cave based, fairly confusing level structure. Every level is distinctly designed and presents their own challenge through getting in, navigating, and getting out.If you're a fan of stealth based gameplay, Thief 2 is all you've ever wanted."
