,Recommended,211740,9102681,"Posted: 14 February, 2014",all,[MM] WMan22,"NOTE:Currently I only have around one hour on steam for this game. That's because I just recently got it to work with steam on a 16:9 resolution and I already beat it several times over way back in the day on windows 98. This gameplay time is currently subject to change whenever I can get the time to beat this game again.Thief 2 is a good sequel to a stealth masterpiece. The map design is much more focused and much more clearly defined than in Thief Gold, which makes for some mildly streamlined but much more sensible map design than in the first; This also introduces entirely new gameplay mechanics (Literally) such as security cam operated sentry guns and robots which lore wise are explained rather well.Developers of the world, this is how you do difficulty modes right.Each difficulty can add new objectives and higher difficulties make the sword a detriment to your inventory as you will often auto-fail a mission for killing someone; You must instead use a blackjack that only works when an enemy is unaware of your presence, which admittedly is sort of broken when you learn how to lean in and blackjack effectively from the shadows. Personally I think it adds to the game to be able to lean in and blackjack, it's a fun abuse of gameplay mechanics, like Bunnyhopping.The sound design is masterfully crafted and unrivalled(for the most part)even today; you're going to want to get a good sound card and some plugins to emulate EAX to really get the proper effect of it.http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k5E0sXdX-Bchttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v6ng_bGozSoBoth Thief Steam releases come with an outdated version of ddfix which allows a few graphical enhancements such as modern resolutions and bloom injection but since the version that comes with the steam release is outdated your game will likely crash immediately upon using a 16:9 resolution in cam.cfg. It's moderately difficult to find the latest version so I'm going to save you the trouble and directly link it.http://rapidlibrary.biz/source.php?file=ulzq8ez8qri89on&url=http%3A%2F%2Fjermi.dyndns.org%2F~jermi%2Fddfix%2Fddfix_1.5.12.zip&sec=893b4f3af5fae4c1Just drop this into your Thief directory where your .exe is and using notepad++ to modify that to whatever graphical improvements you desire, though personally I think bloom looks terrible in any game, let alone injected into one. So i'd just leave it alone and modify cam.cfg so that game_screen_size is 1920 1080 if you're using a 1080p monitor. Hope this helped."
