,Recommended,211740,33467230,Posted: 11 July,all,TheCancerThatKills,"Thief 2: The Metal Age is definitely a diamond from its time. The game is heavy with atmosphere and immerses you within minutes. The story is told through cinematic cutscenes but mostly and solely through the gameplay. You take on the role as Garrett, an experienced thief who steals for a living, throughout the story Garrett becomes entangled within the conflict and mysteries of people and factions. The stealth is very well done, every type of terrain emits a different level of loudness whenever you step on it and allows you to think more strategically for every level. You different types of equipment each with their own uses. For example, you have moss arrows that when shot on the ground it creates a soft surface for you to walk on (very useful for marble floors), water arrows to put out torches and provide more darkness, flash bombs to disorient your enemies and knock them out, and so forth. If you are spotted by guards you'll die in three to four hits, so your best chance of survival is staying behind the shadows. Once you get the hang of everything, you will feel like a master thief.Thief 2 has aged like wine, I can even say it's a masterpiece. It brilliantly combines story, gameplay and atmosphere all at once. If you are a fan of stealth and/or story driven games, then this is a must have."
