,Recommended,211740,20532135,"Posted: 14 January, 2016",all,mech619,"The graphics for this game may not be as spectacular compared to other stealth games like Metal Gear Solid but the gameplay more than makes up for that.Taking place in a Victorian steam punk era with limited amounts of magic, you have to rely on quick wit and your arsenal to advance in the game.Two guards block a doorway you need to enter through.  You could carefully sneak through the dark and bypass them, you could use an arrow to make a sound, drawing them away, or find a hidden passage in the wall to sneak behind them.  This is what makes the game so great, you have options you can use and not keep things so linear.The difficulty also makes the game great.  There is no indicater of any kind to tell you there is a guard on the other side of the wall.  You have to use your ears to listen to footsteps, occasionally whistling, and eyes to see if that guard is carrying a key to unlock a door with.One of the cons I can say about the game is the controls at times can be a little frustrating to deal with.  Sometimes you want to climb up a short wall, quietly, only to have Garrett not only miss grabbing the wall, he may make some noise too, alerting the guards.  I had a similar problem with ladders, with him not dismounting from the well.The cut scenes are kept short and in between each mission.  Most of the story is told from reading parchments, books, and listening to game characters talk amongst themselves.If you're looking for a stealth game that IS superior to most other stealth games, like Metal Gear, I would highly recommend this game ot"
