 gameplay by the time I finished it. I know the thrilling feeling of mastery from T:TDP would come from this game's mechanics as well. It is a well balanced game with a story and setting that is unique and palpable. There are many routes, tactics, and styles of facing obstacles. And, in the end, there are few things better than being Garrett in a dark corner of a huge complex; rifling through every corner, filling my pockets full of gold, and my head full of knowledge that is very much not supposed to belong to me."
