76561198050374800,Not Recommended,211740,11389656,"Posted: 24 July, 2014",all,EnterTheRyGuy,"I don't often write reviews, only under the circumstance whether the game was incredibly enjoyable, or so terrible you'd rather pull your own teeth. This game had me pulling all the newly found gray hairs out of my head, and I was so disappointed. I wish I had the same experience as the other players who write, ""this was one of the best games I've ever played"", but I didn't and I can't fake that I did. It had some shining moments, but were vastly overshadowed (literally) by certain other gameplay characteristics.I feel like I could gripe forever about it but I'll keep it short (I'll try). I did play Thief Gold and enjoyed it a lot. While there were some things I wasn't a fan of, I was able to get over them and still really enjoy the game. Hoping for the same experience in Thief II, I was let down. My biggest gripe of the game, which sounds silly until you play it, is the game is SO. MOTHER. EFFING. DARK. This alone, ruined the game for me. There are 3 or 4 missions I know off the top of my head that I played for 4-5 hours EACH and still couldn't complete the level, only to consult a guide, and only to find out there is a door or ladder or key or something that would advance me in the level. And what held me back from finding it was that it was hidden in the darkest, most pitch black area of a random room. I can't harp on it enough, no matter how much I adjusted the gamma option, or my brightness on my monitor, it never improved. Again sounds silly, but I was physically incapable of finding these things because of it being so dark. The first game was dark too, but not to the extent to where you actually can't see what's ahead of you. There are flares added to the game, but they really don't offer much help. It brightens things up about 1 foot around you, and then disappears after 10 seconds or so.There are other things that bother me about this game, but that is the main one. I almost feel like that if that one thing didn't affect me so much, I'd be able to look past the other things like I did in the first game. I was so determined to beat this game and just completely remove it from my computer. To be stuck in a level for 4-5 hours only to find out that you need to walk through a door in a room you've been in several times already, is something I never want in a game again. Missions like Kidnapped, Casing the Joint, and the final Sabotage at Soulforge, are the bane of my existence in this game. If you buy it, I just hope you have a better experience than I did."
